      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but some people would argue that what you're calling \"censorship\" is actually just people finally being held accountable for harmful or bigoted language that used to be ignored. isn't there a difference between \"silencing dissent\" and just setting social boundaries so people don't get attacked? wouldn't you say that's a necessary part of progress?",
